The paper focuses on object detection in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves a novel tubelet proposal network and a Long Short-term Memory (LSTM) network, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on a large-scale dataset, which is often associated with multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
